Environment setup:
1) https://nodejs.org/en/download/ - Download the node .MSI install package and install the node package on the windows machine.
    a) Once the node MSI file installation is done, open Command Prompt and type node-v
    b) This should display the node version. Example : v6.11.0
    
2) http://brackets.io/ - Download brackets code editor and install the same on the windows machine

3) https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=YVbbdCDBIbI - Explains how to integrate brackets code editor with github





